"aggregated_output\":\"# Active Plan — Codex-Managed-Agent Roadmap Execution\\n\\nPlan anchor: `ROADMAP.md`\\nWorkspace: `/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent`\\nMirror workspace: `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`\\n\\n## Mission\\nExecute `ROADMAP.md` to completion through bounded codex-loop slices. Do not branch into unrelated ideas. After each slice, preserve stability, package the extension, sync the dev mirror, and record a new evolution note.\\n\\n## Milestone Status\\n\\n### Milestone 1 — Architecture Stabilization\\nStatus: mostly complete\\n\\nCompleted:\\n- thin `extension.js`\\n- `src/panel.js` reduced toward orchestration\\n- host modules split into `server`, `codex-link`, `commands`, `auto-continue`, `lifecycle`, `panel-view`, `state-sync`\\n- webview template split into `board`, `insights`, `drawer`\\n\\nRemaining cleanup:\\n- keep `panel.js` from regrowing\\n- prefer new host/webview modules for future work\\n\\n### Milestone 2 — Board Interaction Quality\\nStatus: complete\\n\\nTargets:\\n- improve drag smoothness and drop reliability\\n- finish resize behavior for all supported directions\\n- define clear card-size semantics for `T / S / M / L`\\n- keep `Needs Human` useful without blocking the board\\n- ensure the board remains the single interactive layout surface\\n\\nCompleted in this milestone:\\n- directional board resize now preserves anchored edges for north/west handles and persists the adjusted `col` / `row` / `cols` / `height`\\n- board drop-preview clearing now resets correctly when the pointer leaves card and board boundaries\\n- board density semantics now reserve preview text for `M / L`, keeping `S` as a title-plus-progress tier\\n- `Needs Human` now auto-expands when urgent cards newly appear after an empty state, preventing hidden intervention work\\n- collapsed `Needs Human` now keeps an urgent-count summary visible without reopening the compact dock\\n- compact `Needs Human` cards no longer pulse like main-board intervention cards, reducing visual competition\\n- board drag is now blocked when the gesture starts on card controls, reducing accidental layout edits\\n- board drag-active feedback now appears immediately on dragstart instead of waiting for the first deferred indicator sync\\n- board UI now spells out the `T / S / M / L` size ladder so density semantics are explicit instead of implicit\\n\\nExit review:\\n- drag / resize and compact-surface behavior are now close to the Milestone 2 stability target\\n- `Needs Human` no longer blocks the main board and remains visible in collapsed form\\n- previous size-semantics gap is now addressed in board UI copy\\n- exit confirmation complete: Milestone 2 now satisfies the roadmap exit criteria closely enough to move on\\n\\n### Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer\\nStatus: active\\n\\nTargets:\\n- stabilize usage report generation\\n- improve topic map / word cloud / weekly shift interaction\\n- make guidance more actionable and durable\\n\\nAudit findings:\\n- host-side insights fallback already reads a persisted usage report from `~/.codex/codex_managed_agent_usage_report.json`\\n- webview UI state persists topic-driven navigation state through `vscode.setState()`\\n- first bounded reliability gap: persisted `topicFocus` is not revalidated against current insights data or current threads after reload\\n- host-side persisted-report fallback is sufficient for webview reload recovery; a second reload-survivable webview cache would be redundant right now\\n\\nCompleted in this milestone:\\n- persisted `topicFocus` is now cleared on reload when current thread data no longer supports the saved insight navigation state\\n- active-session insights rendering now reuses the last usable report payload when a transient refresh arrives empty\\n\\nCurrent bounded slice:\\n- make persisted-or-fallback insights state explicit in the UI so users understand when the dashboard is showing cached report data\\n\\n### Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\\nStatus: pending\\n\\nTargets:\\n- background continue observability\\n- clear loop status semantics\\n- degraded-state handling\\n- linked-vs-running distinction across surfaces\\n\\n### Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\\nStatus: pending\\n\\nTargets:\\n- release workflow\\n- screenshots / notes / docs\\n- smoke validation routine\\n- repo structure clarity\\n\\n## Slice Rules\\n- Each tick completes one bounded, verifiable slice only.\\n- Always validate syntax and package builds after code changes.\\n- Always sync export repo changes back to the mirror workspace when behavior changes.\\n- Always append an evolution note in `.claude/plans/loloop/`.\\n- Update this active plan when milestone focus changes.\\n\\n## Immediate Next Slice Queue\\n1. Persisted/fallback insights disclosure pass\\n2. Next bounded usage-report reliability fix after that\\n3. Milestone 4 remains blocked behind Milestone 3\\n4. Milestone 5 remains blocked behind Milestone 4\\n\",\"exit_code\":0,\"status\":\"completed\"}}\n.codex-loop/state/logs/tick_20260414_093606.log:48:{\"type\":\"item.completed\",\"item\":{\"id\":\"item_4\",\"type\":\"command_execution\",\"command\":\"/bin/bash -lc \\\"sed -n '1,220p' .claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-14-m3-reload-fallback-decision.md\\\"\",\"aggregated_output\":\"# Evolution Note — Milestone 3 Reload Fallback Decision\\n\\n## Plan\\n\\n- path: `.claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md`\\n- milestone: `Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer`\\n- bounded target: decide whether the last-known insights snapshot should also survive webview reloads, or whether host-side persistence is already sufficient\\n\\n## Completed\\n\\n- Re-reviewed the host-side insights fallback path in `src/host/server.js`\\n- Re-reviewed the webview-side state persistence path in `src/webview-template.js`\\n- Concluded that host-side persisted report fallback is already the right reload-recovery mechanism for insights dat