 metadata。\\\\n\\\\n实现落点在 [src/host/state-sync.js](/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent/src/host/state-sync.js#L1)。这次没有扩 UI 结构，只把 `.codex-loop/state/thread_id.txt`、`.codex-loop/state/daemon_launcher.json` 和 `.codex-loop/state/daemon_heartbeat.json` 里的最小身份信息拼进已有 daemon card 的 detail 文案里。\\\\n\\\\n我已更新 [codex-loop-control-surface-task-plan.md](/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent/task-plans/codex-loop-control-surface-task-plan.md#L1)，Task 1 的第二项现在已勾掉；[ACTIVE_PLAN.md](/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent/.claude/plans/ACTIVE_PLAN.md#L1) 也已经切回下一步 audit。新的 evolution note 在 [evolution-2026-04-15-loop-control-daemon-metadata.md](/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent/.claude/plans/loloop/evolution-2026-04-15-loop-control-daemon-metadata.md#L1)。\\\\n\\\\n验证已完成：`node --check src/host/state-sync.js`、`node --check src/webview-template.js` 通过，`npm run package` 通过，并重新生成了 [codex-managed-agent-0.0.3.vsix](/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent/codex-managed-agent-0.0.3.vsix)。代码、task-plan、active plan、note 和 VSIX 已同步到 `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`。\\\\n\\\\n下一轮 handoff 保持同一轨道且不扩张：只做一次 Task 1 audit，识别 `daemon metadata` 之后下一个最小的 loop-status gap，不进入 watch/tail 或 runtime controls。\\\"}}\\n.codex-loop/state/logs/tick_20260414_104526.log:55:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_0\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"agent_message\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"使用 `codex-loop` skill 继续这一轮。我会再次按你要求的顺序读取 roadmap、task-plan、active plan 和最新 note，然后只完成当前 Milestone 4 visibility-control 轨道上的一个最小反馈切片。\\\"}}\\n.codex-loop/state/logs/tick_20260414_104526.log:61:{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_3\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/bash -lc \\\\\\\"sed -n '1,260p' .claude/plans/active-codex-managed-agent-roadmap.md\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"# Active Plan — Codex-Managed-Agent Roadmap Execution\\\\n\\\\nPlan anchor: `ROADMAP.md`\\\\nWorkspace: `/home/clashuser/export/codex-managed-agent`\\\\nMirror workspace: `/home/clashuser/hzh/work_bo/codex_manager/vscode-extension`\\\\n\\\\n## Mission\\\\nExecute `ROADMAP.md` to completion through bounded codex-loop slices. Do not branch into unrelated ideas. After each slice, preserve stability, package the extension, sync the dev mirror, and record a new evolution note.\\\\n\\\\n## Milestone Status\\\\n\\\\n### Milestone 1 — Architecture Stabilization\\\\nStatus: mostly complete\\\\n\\\\nCompleted:\\\\n- thin `extension.js`\\\\n- `src/panel.js` reduced toward orchestration\\\\n- host modules split into `server`, `codex-link`, `commands`, `auto-continue`, `lifecycle`, `panel-view`, `state-sync`\\\\n- webview template split into `board`, `insights`, `drawer`\\\\n\\\\nRemaining cleanup:\\\\n- keep `panel.js` from regrowing\\\\n- prefer new host/webview modules for future work\\\\n\\\\n### Milestone 2 — Board Interaction Quality\\\\nStatus: complete\\\\n\\\\nTargets:\\\\n- improve drag smoothness and drop reliability\\\\n- finish resize behavior for all supported directions\\\\n- define clear card-size semantics for `T / S / M / L`\\\\n- keep `Needs Human` useful without blocking the board\\\\n- ensure the board remains the single interactive layout surface\\\\n\\\\nCompleted in this milestone:\\\\n- directional board resize now preserves anchored edges for north/west handles and persists the adjusted `col` / `row` / `cols` / `height`\\\\n- board drop-preview clearing now resets correctly when the pointer leaves card and board boundaries\\\\n- board density semantics now reserve preview text for `M / L`, keeping `S` as a title-plus-progress tier\\\\n- `Needs Human` now auto-expands when urgent cards newly appear after an empty state, preventing hidden intervention work\\\\n- collapsed `Needs Human` now keeps an urgent-count summary visible without reopening the compact dock\\\\n- compact `Needs Human` cards no longer pulse like main-board intervention cards, reducing visual competition\\\\n- board drag is now blocked when the gesture starts on card controls, reducing accidental layout edits\\\\n- board drag-active feedback now appears immediately on dragstart instead of waiting for the first deferred indicator sync\\\\n- board UI now spells out the `T / S / M / L` size ladder so density semantics are explicit instead of implicit\\\\n\\\\nExit review:\\\\n- drag / resize and compact-surface behavior are now close to the Milestone 2 stability target\\\\n- `Needs Human` no longer blocks the main board and remains visible in collapsed form\\\\n- previous size-semantics gap is now addressed in board UI copy\\\\n- exit confirmation complete: Milestone 2 now satisfies the roadmap exit criteria closely enough to move on\\\\n\\\\n### Milestone 3 — Insight and Guidance Layer\\\\nStatus: complete\\\\n\\\\nTargets:\\\\n- stabilize usage report generation\\\\n- improve topic map / word cloud / weekly shift interaction\\\\n- make guidance more actionable and durable\\\\n\\\\nAudit findings:\\\\n- host-side insights fallback already reads a persisted usage report from `~/.codex/codex_managed_agent_usage_report.json`\\\\n- webview UI state persists topic-driven navigation state through `vscode.setState()`\\\\n- first bounded reliability gap: persisted `topicFocus` is not revalidated against current insights data or current threads after reload\\\\n- host-side persisted-report fallback is sufficient for webview reload recovery; a second reload-survivable webview cache would be redundant right now\\\\n\\\\nCompleted in this milestone:\\\\n- persisted `topicFocus` is now cleared on reload when current thread data no longer supports the saved insight navigation state\\\\n- active-session insights rendering now reuses the last usable report payload when a transient refresh arrives empty\\\\n- insights UI now explicitly discloses when it is showing persisted fallback data or an in-session cached report\\\\n- insights disclosure now includes a freshness timestamp for persisted fallback data and in-session cached reports\\\\n- persisted fallback insights now get explicit stale wording once the cached report is older than a simple 24-hour threshold\\\\n- topic-map-driven thread filtering now exposes an explicit clear-focus action directly in the thread summary surface\\\\n- active `topicFocus` now highlights the matching topic-map node so the filtered target stays visually legible\\\\n- weekly report now includes one concise next-action cue derived from the strongest weekly shift when available\\\\n\\\\nExit review:\\\\n- current insights persistence/disclosure flow now covers reload fallback, in-session cache reuse, source disclosure, freshness disclosure, and stale wording\\\\n- topic-map/thread-list linkage now covers click-to-filter, reload-safe focus validation, explicit clear-focus, and active-node highlighting\\\\n- weekly report now includes one concise next-action cue, satisfying the remaining actionability gap closely enough for this milestone\\\\n- exit confirmation complete: Milestone 3 now satisfies the roadmap exit criteria closely enough to move on\\\\n\\\\n### Milestone 4 — Operational Reliability\\\\nStatus: active\\\\n\\\\nTargets:\\\\n- background continue observability\\\\n- clear loop status semantics\\\\n- degraded-state handling\\\\n- linked-vs-running distinction across surfaces\\\\n\\\\nAudit findings:\\\\n- host-side auto-continue state already records `armed / queued / running / failed / success`, plus the last log path and last result detail\\\\n- detailed loop state is currently visible inside larger board cards, but not in the compact thread-list scanning surface\\\\n- first bounded reliability gap: users cannot quickly scan which threads have an armed, queued, running, or failed auto-loop without opening richer card UI\\\\n- current visibility controls are split across low-level `Open Codex`, `Sidebar Codex`, `Archive`, `Unarchive`, and `Rename` actions instead of a roadmap-level `Show in Codex / Hide from Codex` path\\\\n- first practical visibility-control gap is missing explicit `Show in Codex`: host primitives already support rename, unarchive, and Codex open, but the drawer does not yet bundle them into one intentional action\\\\n\\\\nExit review:\\\\n- thread rows now expose compact loop state, while larger board cards still retain the richer log/result detail path\\\\n- this is enough to satisfy the immediate loop-status scanning gap without changing host-side detached resume behavior\\\\n- explorer grouping now gives `linked` threads a dedicated bucket instead of folding them into generic idle\\\\n- spotlight now exposes a compact auto-loop log action, so log access is no longer confined to larger board cards\\\\n- degraded-state recovery now exposes a direct service-log action instead of plain log-path text\\\\n- spotlight now exposes the compact auto-loop state directly, which is sufficient for this inspector-level status gap\\\\n- visibility-control audit complete: the missing piece is not another host primitive, but one explicit drawer-level `Show in Codex` action that can unarchive before opening the target thread in Codex\\\\n- drawer-level `Show in Codex` now follows the first practical visibility path: best-effort title sync, unarchive, then open the target thread in Codex\\\\n- drawer-level `Hide from Codex` now maps the existing clean archive path to the roadmap language without changing delete semantics or extension-side state handling\\\\n\\\\nCurrent bounded slice:\\\\n- add one drawer-level visibility status metric that makes `visible / hidden / linked / focused` state explicit\\\\n\\\\n### Milestone 5 — Publishable Product Quality\\\\nStatus: pending\\\\n\\\\nTargets:\\\\n- release workflow\\\\n- screenshots / notes / docs\\\\n- smoke validation routine\\\\n- repo structure clarity\\\\n\\\\n## Slice Rules\\\\n- Each tick completes one bounded, verifiable slice only.\\\\n- Always validate syntax and package builds after code changes.\\